title.narrative: 404 PROVIDE PROTECTION SERVICES FOR CHILDREN & ADOLESCENTS DURING COVID-19

description.narrative: Governments and partners have increased capacity to provide critical protection services for children and adolescents, in response to the COVID outbreak., which contributes to Access To Justice, Access To Justice (Covid), Adolescent Empowerment, Adolescent Empowerment (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022
